.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-7-19::.
6 different pets are kept: guinea-pig, fish, frog, hamster, chinchilla, pony
The people use 6 different means of transport: helicopter, jet-ski, subway, ship, snowmobile, taxi
 1. the person driving the subway is the owner of the frog##1
 2. the owner of the guinea-pig is in an odd position##4
 3. the owner of the fish is on the left of the person driving the taxi##1
 4. the owner of the fish is on the left or right of the owner of the chinchilla##3
 5. the owner of the hamster is somewhere to the left of the person driving the subway##5
 6. the owner of the guinea-pig is between the owner of the chinchilla and the person driving the helicopter##2
 7. the person driving the taxi is somewhere to the left of the person driving the jet-ski##5
 8. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left or right of the person driving the helicopter##3
 9. the owner of the fish is in an odd position##4
10. the owner of the frog is somewhere to the right of the person driving the taxi##5
11. the owner of the hamster is on the left of the owner of the pony##1
12. the person driving the snowmobile is somewhere between the owner of the frog and the person driving the jet-ski##7
13. the owner of the chinchilla is somewhere to the left of the owner of the pony##5

.:: Answer ::.
|             |   1   |   2    |     3     |   4    |  5   |     6      |
| Pet         | fish   | chinchilla | guinea-pig      | hamster | pony  | frog   |
| Transport   | ship | taxi  | jet-ski | helicopter   | snowmobile | subway |

